--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Origin and third-party notes
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

libre's client is original code written from scratch in vanilla JavaScript. It
does NOT incorporate source code from any third-party application.

NIP-72 event kinds, tag names, and the Nostr wire format used here are facts
defined by the public Nostr protocol specifications (NIPs), not copyrightable
material of any implementation.

During development, the project andotherstuff/chorus (a React NIP-72 client) was
consulted as a behavioral reference for NIP-72 flows. Its source is kept locally
under reference/ for study only and is excluded from this repository's
distribution (see .gitignore). No chorus source code is shipped in libre. If in
the future any specific chorus code is ported, the MIT license notice for that
code must be preserved alongside it, per that project's stated MIT licensing.

